The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Stock split on Gammon agenda

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, Feb. 1: Gammon India Ltd will sub-divide the value of its shares to Rs 2 apiece from Rs 10. 

 The company will seek shareholders? permission at an extraordinary general meeting on February 28, Gammon has informed the stock exchanges. Gammon said the EGM will also consider alternation of the terms of remuneration for the chairman and managing director and certain ?key officials of the management?.

 On the Bombay Stock Exchange today, the Gammon scrip, after opening at Rs 738, shot up to an intra-day high of Rs 760 and ended at Rs 745.35.

 Last year, Gammon India had announced that it will issue 21.78 lakh shares on preferential allotment to Uno Investments, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Chrys Capital III LLC at a price of Rs 505 per share. 




